caption.text:
This post is a tribute for my favorite place to hangout in Bandung, probably the coziest place I've encountered in the past 2 years. 
So today I went there, and there is a garage sale for ALL those second-hand books, 50-70% on all different kind of books, starting today until tomorrow. And I was beyond happy, almost all the shelves were empty (trust me, that was weird), and I was like "where are the books?!", but my happy self turned sad when I discovered that Reading Lights is going to close for a long time, I don't know if it's temporary or not but I pray to God that it is. So I sat at my fav chair (the sofa that overlooked the window), and just sat there. My God, I am so sad. 
Sorry for the long caption, but I need to say it. Reading Lights, you are forever in my heartüíï

Pict by: @han.poh
